<p><strong>Bitcoin is holding the $66,000 support level</strong> after a -5.64% selloff that briefly tested $65,800 overnight. For meme coin traders, this is the exact setup that historically precedes the most profitable accumulation windows of the cycle.</p>

<p>BTC dominance at 55.99%, elevated volume at $139B (+17%), and altcoins down harder than Bitcoin ” this is not a market to panic in. It's a market to prepare in. Here's the exact accumulation strategy for meme coin positioning, with specific targets for <strong>$DKING (DogeKing)</strong> in the rotation ahead.</p>

<h2>Why $66K Support Matters More Than Any Other Level</h2>

<p>The $66,000 zone has been tested three times in the past 30 days:</p>

<ul>
<li><strong>May 8:</strong> BTC touched $65,700 �™ bounced to $69,400 (+5.6%)</li>
<li><strong>May 22:</strong> BTC touched $65,900 �™ bounced to $71,200 (+8.0%)</li>
<li><strong>June 3:</strong> BTC touched $65,800 �™ currently holding $66,700</li>
</ul>

<p>Three touches of the same support zone without a breakdown is a textbook accumulation pattern. Each test strengthens the level because sellers get exhausted while buyers step in at the same price. The third touch is often the final shakeout before a reversal.</p>

