<h2>Risk Management: The Other Side of the Trade</h2>

<p>No strategy works 100% of the time. Here's the risk framework for this accumulation setup:</p>

<div class="warning-box">
<h3>⚠ Invalidation Scenarios</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>BTC loses $65K</strong> ” If BTC breaks below $65K on increasing volume, the support is broken. Immediately pause all new accumulation. Reduce positions by 50% until $62K is tested.</li>
<li><strong>BTC.D pushes above 58%</strong> ” If dominance continues rising while BTC falls, risk-off is deepening. Move to stablecoins. Wait for BTC.D to peak above 60% before re-entering.</li>
<li><strong>Volume collapses below $80B</strong> ” If 24h total volume drops below $80B, market interest is fading. The setup is invalidated regardless of price action.</li>
</ul>
</div>

<h2>The Bottom Line</h2>

<p>Bitcoin at $66,700 with a third touch of the $66K support zone, BTC.D at 56% with surging volume, and meme coins showing extreme relative strength on the selloff ” this is not a market to fear. This is the accumulation zone that separates prepared traders from reactive ones.</p>

<p><strong>$DKING (DogeKing)</strong> is positioned as the highest-conviction meme coin for this rotation, with proven relative strength, a growing content ecosystem on dogeking.us (300+ articles), and a community that holds through volatility.</p>

<p>The strategy is simple: prepare now, deploy on the signal, and let the rotation do the work. BTC.D at 56% won't last forever ” and when it breaks, meme coin season could arrive faster than anyone expects.</p>

